  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/engineering/domains/domesticity/domains/production/gardening/terms/plantain-herb/> ;
  schema:name "Plantain Herb" ;
  schema:description "Perennial cultivar of Plantago major, hardy zones 3-9. Basal rosette of broad ribbed leaves. Ubiquitous \"weed\" medicinal with multi-civilizational use (Ayurveda, TCM, Traditional Persian Medicine, Ojibwe/Iroquois/Menominee herbalism). Leaf poultice heals wounds, insect bites, inflamed skin—universal vulnerary application. Easy to cultivate anywhere; prefers moist, moderately fertile soil but tolerates poor soils. Harvest young leaves spring-summer for maximum potency. Dried leaves steep as throat-soothing tea." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-04-02" ;
